obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20701)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20701&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Small Industries`
  line `Development Bank of India Act, 1989.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint and`
  line `different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 7th March, 1990, vide notification No. S.O. 197(E), dated 7th March, 1990, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20702)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20702&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Board of directors of the Small Industries Development Bank of India`
  line `referred to in section 5;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) "chairman and managing director" means the chairman and managing director referred to in`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 6;]`
  line
  line `(c) "Court" means the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(i) the defendant or respondent or, where there is more than one defendant or respondent, any`
  line `one of them--`
  line
  line `(1) has his registered office, or`
  line
  line `(2) carries on the whole or part of his business,`
  line
  line `at the time of commencement of any legal proceedings against him under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the cause of action for such legal proceedings, wholly or in part, arises;`
  line
  line `(d) "Development Bank" means the Industrial Development Bank of India established under`
  line `section 3 of the Industrial Development Bank of India Act,1964 (18 of 1964);`
  line
  line `(e) "Director" means a Director nominated under sub-section (1) of section 6 and includes`
  line `the ^2`
  line `[chairman and managing director and whole-time director];`
  line
  line `(f) "export" means export from India of products or services of any industrial concern in`
  line `small-scale sector;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(fa) "General Insurance Corporation" means the General Insurance Corporation of India`
  line `formed under section 9 of the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972);]`
  line
  line `(g) "import" means import into India of services or goods including all materials, commodities`
  line `and articles in a solid, liquid or gaseous state and all forms of energy for the use of any industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(h) "industrial concern in the small scale sector" means any concern engaged or to be engaged`
  line in,--
  line
  line `(i) the manufacture, preservation or processing of goods;`
  line
  line `(ii) shipping;`
  line
  line `(iii) mining including development of mines;`
  line
  line `(iv) the hotel industry;`
  line
  line `(v) the transport of passengers or goods by road or by water or by air or by ropeway or by lift;`
  line
  line `(vi) the generation, storage or distribution of electricity or any other form of energy;`
  line
  line `(vii) the maintenance, repair, testing or servicing of machinery or equipment of any`
  line `description or vehicles or vessels or motor boats or trailers or tractors;`
  line
  line `(viii) assembling, repairing or packing any article with the aid of machinery or power;`
  line
  line `(ix) the setting up of, or development of, an industrial area or an industrial estate;`
  line
  line `(x) fishing or providing shore facilities for fishing or maintenance thereof;`
  line
  line `(xi) providing special or technical knowledge or other services for the promotion of industrial`
  line growth;
  line
  line `(xii) providing engineering, technical, financial, management, marketing or other services or`
  line `facilities for industry;`
  line
  line `(xiii) service industry such as altering, ornamenting, polishing, finishing, oiling, washing,`
  line `cleaning or otherwise treating or adapting any article or substance with a view to its use, sale,`
  line `transport, delivery or disposal;`
  line
  line `(xiv) providing medical, health or other allied services;`
  line
  line `(xv) providing services relating to information technology, telecommunication or electronics;`
  line
  line `(xvi) leasing, sub-leasing or giving on hire-purchase of industrial plants, equipments,`
  line `machinery or other assets including vehicles, ships and aircraft;`
  line
  line `(xvii) such other activity as the Central Government may, having regard to the objects of this`
  line `Act, by notification, specify in this behalf; or`
  line
  line `(xviii) the research and development of any concept, technology, design, process or product`
  line `whether in relation to any of the matters aforesaid, including any activities specified under`
  line `sub-clause (xvii), or any other matter and which is regarded as a small-scale undertaking under`
  line `section 11B of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951(65 of 1951);`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The expression "processing of goods" includes any art or process for producing,`
  line `preparing or making an article by subjecting any material to a manual, mechanical, chemical, electrical or`
  line `any other like operation.]`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(ha) "Life Insurance Corporation" means the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under`
  line `section 3 of the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);]`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) "National Small Industries Corporation" means the National Small Industries Corporation Limited`
  line `registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(k) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(la) "public sector bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act,`
  line `1959 (38 of 1959), a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies`
  line `(Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980);]`
  line
  line ^8
  line `(lb) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(lc) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `(m) "Small Industries Bank" means the Small Industries Development Bank of India established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(n) "State Small Industries Corporation" means a State Corporation, registered under the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), for small industries in a State;`
  line
  line `(o) "State Financial Corporation" means a financial corporation established under section 3 or section`
  line `3A or an institution notified under section 46 of the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951);`
  line
  line `(p) "State Industrial Development Corporation" means a State Corporation registered under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) for the development of industries in a State;`
  line
  line ^9
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 7 of 2000, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs, by s. 2, ibid., for "Managing Director" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 2003, s. 2, and The Schedule (w.e.f. 2-7-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (i) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 53 of 2003, s. 12 and The Schedule (w.e.f. 2-7-2004).`
  line
  line `9. Clause (q) omitted by s. 12 and The Schedule, ibid. (2-7-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20703)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Small Industries Development Bank of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20703&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With`
  line `effect from such date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established,`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, a corporation to be known as the Small Industries Development Bank of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The Small Industries Bank shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and`
  line `dispose of property and to contract, and may, by that name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Small Industries Bank shall be at Lucknow or at such other place as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The Small Industries Bank shall establish offices, branches or agencies at any place in or outside`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20704)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Authorised capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20704&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Authorised capital.--The authorised capital of the Small Industries Bank shall be one thousand`
  line `crores of rupees divided into seventy-five crores fully paid-up equity shares of rupees ten each and`
  line `twenty-five crores of fully paid-up redeemable preference shares of rupees ten each:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Board, by notification,`
  line `increase the authorised capital to an amount not exceeding two thousand crores of rupees consisting of`
  line `such number of equity shares and redeemable preference shares as it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (20705)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Conversion of equity shares into redeemable preference shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20705&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Conversion of equity shares into redeemable preference shares.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, at any time after the commencement of the Small Industries Development Bank of`
  line `India (Amendment) Act, 2000, by notification, convert such number of equity shares held by the`
  line `Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government, not exceeding twentyfive`
  line `crores, as it may decide, into redeemable preference shares:`
  line
  line `Provided that such conversion shall in no case reduce the equity shares held in aggregate by the`
  line `Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government to less than fifty-one`
  line `per cent.`
  line
  line `(2) The redeemable preference shares referred to in sub-section (1) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) carry such fixed rate of dividend as the Central Government may specify at the time of such`
  line `conversion, and`
  line
  line `(b) neither be transferable nor carry any voting rights.`
  line
  line `(3) The redeemable preference shares referred to in sub-section (1) shall be redeemed by the Small`
  line `Industries Bank within three years from the date of such conversion in such instalments and in such`
  line `manner as the Board may determine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (20706)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20706&sectionno=4B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Transfer of capital.--On such date as the Central Government may, in consultation with the`
  line `Development Bank, by notification, specify (hereinafter referred to as "the specified date"), not less than`
  line `fifty-one per cent. of the issued capital of the Small Industries Bank which has been subscribed by the`
  line `Development Bank as on the date immediately preceding the specified date shall, stand transferred to, and`
  line `vested in, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance Corporation and`
  line `other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government in such proportion, manner and on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be determined by that Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_c:
  sectionId (20707)
  sectionNo 4C
  orderNo 7
  title `Issued capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20707&sectionno=4C&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[4C. Issued capital.--(1) The issued capital, of the Small Industries Bank, of four hundred and fifty`
  line `crores of rupees, immediately before the commencement of the Small Industries Development Bank of`
  line `India (Amendment) Act, 2000, shall, on such commencement, stand divided into forty-five crores equity`
  line `shares of rupees ten each.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, increase the issued equity share capital or redeemable`
  line `preference share capital of the Small Industries Bank by allotment of shares to such persons and on such`
  line `terms and conditions as the Board may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that no increase in the issued equity capital shall be made in such a manner that the`
  line `Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government, hold in aggregate at`
  line `any time, less than fifty-one per cent. of the issued equity share capital of the Small Industries Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_d:
  sectionId (20708)
  sectionNo 4D
  orderNo 8
  title `Reduction of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20708&sectionno=4D&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[4D. Reduction of share capital.--(1) The Small Industries Bank may, with the prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by a resolution passed in a general meeting of the shareholders, reduce its share`
  line `capital in any way.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the share capital may be reduced by--`
  line
  line `(a) extinguishing or reducing the liability on any of its equity shares in respect of the share capital`
  line `not paid-up;`
  line
  line `(b) either with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its equity shares,`
  line `cancelling any paid-up share capital which is lost, or is unrepresented by available assets; or`
  line
  line `(c) either with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its equity shares, paying`
  line `off any paid-up share capital which is in excess of the wants of the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) In any general meeting referred to in sub-section (1), the resolution for reduction of share capital`
  line `shall be passed by shareholders entitled to vote, voting in person, or, where proxies are allowed, by proxy, and the votes cast in favour of the resolution are not less than three times the number of the votes, if any,`
  line `cast against the resolution by shareholders so entitled and voting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_e:
  sectionId (20709)
  sectionNo 4E
  orderNo 9
  title `Restriction on exercising of voting right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20709&sectionno=4E&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[4E. Restriction on exercising of voting right.--Every shareholder of the Small Industries Bank`
  line `holding equity shares shall have a right to vote in respect of such shares on every resolution and his`
  line `voting right on a poll shall be in proportion to his share of the paid-up equity share capital of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided, however, that no shareholder, other than the Development Bank, the public sector banks,`
  line `the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance Corporation and other institutions owned or`
  line `controlled by the Central Government, shall be entitled to exercise voting rights in respect of any equity`
  line `shares held by him in excess of ten per cent. of the issued equity share capital.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20710)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 10
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20710&sectionno=5&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Management.(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of affairs and`
  line `business of the Small Industries Bank shall vest in a Board of Directors which may exercise all powers`
  line `and do all such acts and things as may be exercised or done by the Small Industries Bank and are not by`
  line `this Act expressly directed or required to be done by the Small Industries Bank in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall also be exercisable in`
  line `such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified by it, by the chairman and managing`
  line `director or the whole-time directors.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board in discharging its functions shall act on`
  line `business principles with due regard to public interest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20711)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 11
  title `Constitution of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 3, for sections 4 to 6 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20711&sectionno=6&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Constitution of Board.--(1) The Board shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a chairman and managing director appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) two whole-time directors appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) two directors who shall be officials of the Central Government nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) three directors to be nominated in the prescribed manner by the Development Bank, the public`
  line `sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance Corporation and other institutions`
  line `owned or controlled by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) three directors, including one Director from the officials of the State Financial Corporations,`
  line `nominated by the Central Government from amongst the persons having special knowledge of, or`
  line `professional experience in, science, technology, economics, industry, banking, industrial cooperatives,`
  line `law, industrial finance, investment, accountancy, marketing or any other matter, the`
  line `special knowledge of, or professional experience in, which would, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, be useful to the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(f) such number of directors not exceeding four elected in the prescribed manner, by shareholders,`
  line `other than the Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the`
  line `Life Insurance Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government,`
  line `whose names are entered in the register of shareholders of the Small Industries Bank ninety days`
  line `before the date of the meeting in which such election takes place on the following basis, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is ten per cent.`
  line `or less of the total issued equity share capital, two directors;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is more than ten`
  line `per cent. but less than twenty-five per cent. of the total issued equity share capital, three directors;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is twenty-five`
  line `per cent. or more of the total issued equity share capital, four directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the percentage of holding of issued equity share capital with the shareholders, other`
  line `than the Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General Insurance Corporation, the Life`
  line `Insurance Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government, does not`
  line `permit election of four directors or until the assumption of charge by the elected directors, the Board may`
  line `at any time co-opt such number of directors, not exceeding four, from amongst the persons having special`
  line `knowledge of, or professional experience in, science, technology, economics, industry, banking, industrial`
  line `co-operatives, law, industrial finance, investment, accountancy, marketing or any other matter, the special`
  line `knowledge of, or professional experience in, which would, in the opinion of the Board, be useful to the`
  line `Small Industries Bank for carrying out its functions, who shall hold office until the assumption of charge`
  line `by the elected directors and an equal number of such co-opted directors shall retire in the order of`
  line co-option.
  line
  line `(2) The chairman and managing director and the whole-time directors shall hold office for such term`
  line `not exceeding five years as the Central Government may specify in this behalf and any person so`
  line `appointed shall be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the term of office of the chairman and managing director or the whole-time director, as`
  line `the case may be, at any time before the expiry of the term specified under sub-section (2) by giving him`
  line `notice of not less than three months in writing or three months salary and allowances in lieu of such`
  line `notice and the chairman and managing director or the whole-time director, as the case may be, shall also`
  line `have the right to relinquish his office at any time before the expiry of the term specified under`
  line `sub-section (2) by giving, the Central Government, notice of not less than three months in writing.`
  line
  line `(4) The chairman and managing director and the whole-time directors shall receive such salary and`
  line `allowances, as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, at any time, remove the chairman and managing director or the`
  line `whole-time director, as the case may be, from office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed from his office, under this sub-section, unless he has been`
  line `given an opportunity of showing cause against his removal.`
  line
  line `(6) Every Director nominated under clauses (c), (d) and (e) of sub-section (1), shall hold office during`
  line `the pleasure of the authority nominating him.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (6),--`
  line
  line `(a) every Director nominated under clauses (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) shall hold office for`
  line `such term not exceeding three years as the Central Government, or the authority nominating him, as`
  line `the case may be, may specify in this behalf and thereafter until his successor assumes office, and shall`
  line `be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such Director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years; and`
  line
  line `(b) every Director elected under clause (f) of sub-section (1) shall hold office for three years and`
  line `thereafter until his successor assumes office and shall be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.`
  line
  line `(8) The shareholders, other than the Development Bank, the public sector banks, the General`
  line `Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance Corporation and other institutions owned or controlled by the`
  line `Central Government may, after giving the director a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, by resolution passed by majority of the votes of such shareholders holding in the`
  line `aggregate not less than one-half of the equity share capital held by such shareholders, remove any director`
  line `elected under clause (f) of sub-section (1) and elect another director in his place to fill the vacancy so`
  line caused.
  line
  line `(9) (i) A meeting of the Board shall be held at least once in every three months and at least four`
  line `meetings shall be held every year and the meetings may be held at such places as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(ii) Notice of every meeting of the Board shall be given in writing to every Director for the time being`
  line `in India, and at his usual address in India to every other Director.`
  line
  line `(10) Subject to the provisions contained in this Chapter, the Board may meet at such times and places`
  line `and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of its business including the manner of`
  line `adoption of resolutions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(11) The chairman and managing director, if for any reason, is unable to attend a meeting of the`
  line `Board, any other Director nominated by the chairman and managing director in this behalf and in the`
  line `absence of such nomination, any director elected by the directors present from among themselves, shall`
  line `preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(12) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the directors present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the chairman and`
  line `managing director, or in his absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(13) Save as provided in sub-section (12), every Director of the Board shall have one vote.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20712)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 12
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20712&sectionno=7&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `7. [Managing Director.]--Omitted by the Small Industries Development Bank of India (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2000 (7 of 2000) s. 4 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20713)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 13
  title `Disqualification of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 5, for sections 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20713&sectionno=8&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Disqualifications of directors.-- A person shall not be eligible for being elected as a director`
  line `under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 6, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been found to be of unsound mind by a court of competent jurisdiction and the finding is`
  line `in force;`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) has applied to be adjudicated as an insolvent and his application is pending;`
  line
  line `(d) has been convicted by a court of competent jurisdiction, of any offence involving moral`
  line `turpitude and sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months and a period`
  line `of five years has not elapsed from the date of expiry of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(e) has not paid any call in respect of shares of the Small Industries Bank held by him, whether`
  line `alone or jointly with others, and six months have elapsed from the last day fixed for the payment of`
  line `the call.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20714)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 14
  title `Vacation and resignation of office by directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 5, for sections 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20714&sectionno=9&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Vacation and resignation of office by directors.--(1) The office of a director shall become`
  line `vacant if he--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 8; or`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his office by giving notice in writing under his hand and the resignation is accepted; or`
  line
  line `(c) absents himself from three consecutive meetings of the Board without obtaining leave of`
  line `absence from the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (a) of sub-section (1), the disqualifications referred`
  line `to in that clause shall not take effect--`
  line
  line `(a) for thirty days from the date of the adjudication, sentence or order;`
  line
  line `(b) where any appeal or petition is preferred within thirty days aforesaid against the adjudication,`
  line `sentence or conviction resulting in the sentence or order until the expiry of seven days from the date`
  line `on which such appeal or petition is disposed of; or`
  line
  line `(c) where within the seven days aforesaid, any further appeal or petition is preferred in respect of`
  line `the adjudication, sentence, conviction or order and the appeal or petition, if allowed, would result in`
  line `the removal of the disqualification, until such further appeal or petition is disposed of.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20715)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 15
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
