obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20717)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title `Executive Committee and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 7, for section 12 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20717&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Executive Committee and other committees.-- (1) The Board shall constitute an Executive`
  line `Committee consisting of the chairman and managing director, the whole-time directors and such other`
  line `directors as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall discharge such functions as may be prescribed or as may, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions contained in section 34, be delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may constitute such other committees whether consisting wholly of directors or wholly`
  line `of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons for such purpose or purposes as it may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Committee or any other committee constituted under this section shall meet at such`
  line `times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (20718)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 18
  title `Fees and allowances of directors and members of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 7, for section 12 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20718&sectionno=12A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Fees and allowances of directors and members of committees.--The directors and the`
  line `members of a committee shall be paid such fees and allowances as may be prescribed for attending the`
  line `meetings of the Board or of any committee constituted in pursuance of this Act and for attending to any`
  line `other work of the Small Industries Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fees shall be payable to the chairman and managing director or to the whole-time`
  line `directors or to any other director who is an official of the Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20719)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 19
  title `Business of Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20719&sectionno=13&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small Industries Bank shall function as the`
  line `principal financial institution for the promotion, financing and development of industrial concerns in the`
  line `small-scale sector and shall also coordinate the functions of institutions engaged in promoting, financing`
  line `and developing the industrial concerns in the small-scale sector and may carry on and transact any of the`
  line `following business, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(i) granting loans and advances to any State Financial Corporation, State Industrial`
  line `Development Corporation, State Small Industries Corporation, scheduled bank, State Cooperative`
  line `Bank or such other financial institutions, approved by the Board in this behalf, by way of refinance on`
  line `such terms and conditions as it may deem fit to impose, of any loans or advances granted to industrial`
  line `concerns in the small-scale sector by such corporation, bank, or institution or, of any loans or`
  line `advances granted by the State Financial Corporation or State Industrial Development Corporation to`
  line `any other industrial concern, which are repayable within a period not exceeding twenty-five years;]`
  line
  line `(ii) accepting, discounting or rediscounting bills of exchange and promissory notes made, drawn,`
  line `accepted or endorsed by industrial concerns in the small-scale sector or by any person selling`
  line `products manufactured by an industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(iii) subscribing to, or purchasing stocks, shares bonds or debentures of, any State Financial`
  line `Corporation, State Industrial Development Corporation, State Small Industries Corporation, National`
  line `Small Industries Corporation or ^2[such other financial institutions as may be approved by the Board in`
  line `this behalf];`
  line
  line `(iv) granting lines of credit or loans and advances to any State Financial Corporation, State`
  line `Industrial Development Corporation, State Small Industries Corporation, National Small Industries`
  line `Corporation or ^2[such other financial institutions as may be approved by the Board in this behalf];`
  line
  line `(v) granting loans and advances to any industrial concern in the small-scale sector or subscribing`
  line `to, or purchasing, or under-writing the issue of stocks, shares, bonds or debentures of, any such`
  line `concern:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to preclude the Small Industries`
  line `Bank from granting loans or advances to, or subscribing to the debentures of, an industrial concern in`
  line `the small-scale sector, the amounts outstanding thereon may be convertible at the option of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank into stocks or shares of that concern within the period of loan, advance or debenture`
  line `is repayable.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, the expression "the amounts outstanding thereon" used in relation to`
  line `any loan or advance, shall mean the principal, interest and other charges payable on such loan or`
  line `advance as at the time when the amounts are sought to be converted into stocks or shares;`
  line
  line `(vi) granting loans and advances--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person exporting; or`
  line
  line `(b) to any person outside India, in connection with the export; or`
  line
  line `(c) for the execution of turn-key projects outside India by any industrial concern in the smallscale`
  line sector;
  line
  line `(vii) granting loans and advances to a scheduled bank or any other bank or such financial`
  line `institutions ^3[approved by the Board in this behalf], by way of refinance of loans and advances`
  line `granted by it for purposes of export;`
  line
  line `(viii) accepting, collecting, discounting, rediscounting, purchasing, selling or negotiating in or`
  line `outside India, bills of exchange or promissory notes arising out of transactions, relating to export or`
  line `import and granting of loans and advances in or outside India against such bills or promissory notes;`
  line
  line `(ix) granting, opening, issuing, confirming or endorsing letters of credit and negotiating or`
  line `collecting bills or other documents drawn thereunder;`
  line
  line `(x) granting lines of credit to the Government of any foreign State or any financial institution or`
  line `person outside India for the purpose of export or import;`
  line
  line `(xi) financing export from or import into India of machinery, equipment or other assets including`
  line `vehicles, ships and aircrafts on lease, sub-lease or hire purchase basis by or for any industrial concern`
  line `in small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xii) buying or selling of, or entering into such other dealings in, foreign exchange, as may be`
  line `necessary for the discharge of the functions of the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(xiii) opening of any account in any bank in or outside India or making of any agency`
  line `arrangements with, or acting as an agent or correspondent of, any bank or other institution in or`
  line `outside India;`
  line
  line `(xiv) transferring for consideration any instrument relating to loans and advances granted by it to`
  line `any industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xv) granting loans and advances to any person for purposes of investment in any industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xvi) guaranteeing loans raised from, or credit arrangements made with, any bank, financial`
  line `institution or other lending agency in any country outside India in foreign currency, with the approval`
  line `of the Central Government, by industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xvii) guaranteeing deferred payments due from any industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xviii) guaranteeing--`
  line
  line `(a) loans raised by industrial concerns in the small-scale sector which are floated in the public`
  line `market, or`
  line
  line `(b) loans raised by any industrial concern in the small-scale sector from any scheduled bank`
  line `or State Co-operative Bank or State Financial Corporation or State Industrial Corporation or such`
  line `other financial institutions ^4[as approved by the Board in this behalf];`
  line
  line `(xix) guaranteeing the obligations of any scheduled bank or State Co-operative Bank or State`
  line `Financial Corporation or State Industrial Development Corporation or State Small Industries`
  line `Corporation or such other financial institutions ^4[as approved by the Board in this behalf], arising out`
  line `of, or in connection with, underwriting the issue of stocks, shares, bonds or debentures of any`
  line `industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xx) providing factoring services to any industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xxi) providing technical and financial consultancy, merchant banking and extension services;`
  line
  line `(xxii) undertaking activities for promotion of industry in the small-scale sector including`
  line `entrepreneural development programmes, raw material purchase, marketing support and promotion`
  line `of, or financial support to, agencies engaged in such activities;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) acquiring, with the approval of ^5[the Central Government], the undertaking including the`
  line `business, assets and liabilities of any institution the principal object of which is the promotion or`
  line `development of industry in the small-scale sector in India, or the grant of financial assistance for such`
  line `promotion or development;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) leasing, sub-leasing or giving on hire or hire-purchase any movable or immovable assets to`
  line `any industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xxv) undertaking research and surveys for evaluating or dealing with marketing or investments`
  line `and undertaking and carrying on techno-economic studies in connection with the development of`
  line `industry in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) providing technical, legal, marketing and administrative assistance to any industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector or any person for promotion, management or expansion of any`
  line `industrial concern in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) planning, promoting and developing industries in the small-scale sector;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) promoting, forming or conducting or associating in the promotion, formation or conduct`
  line `of companies, subsidiaries, societies, trusts or such other association of persons as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(xxix) acting as agent of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or of the Reserve Bank or of the Development Bank, or`
  line
  line `(b) such other Government or person as ^6[the Board] may authorise;`
  line
  line `(xxx) doing any other kind of business which the Central Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of ^6[the Board], authorise;`
  line
  line `(xxxi) generally doing such other acts and things as may be incidental to, or consequential upon,`
  line `the exercise of its powers or the discharge of its duties under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force including sale or transfer of any of its assets.`
  line
  line `(2) The Small Industries Bank may receive in consideration of any of the services mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) such commission, brokerage, interest, remuneration or fees as may be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(3) The Small Industries Bank shall not grant any loan or advance or other financial accommodation`
  line `on the security of its own bonds or debentures.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "such other financial institutions, as the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the`
  line `Development Bank, specify" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 8, for "as the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Development Bank, specify"`
  line `(w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 8, for "as the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Development Bank, specify"`
  line `(w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "the Central Government on the recommendation of the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20720)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 20
  title `Loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20720&sectionno=14&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after the due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, advance to the Small Industries Bank--`
  line
  line `(a) an interest free loan of such amount and repayable in such instalments and in such other`
  line `manner as may be determined by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) such further sums of money by way of loan on such terms and conditions as may be agreed`
  line `upon:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, on a request being made to it by the Small Industries`
  line `Bank, increase the number of instalments or alter the amount of any instalment or vary the date on which`
  line `any instalment is payable under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20721)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 21
  title `Borrowings and acceptance of deposits by the Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 9, for "approved by the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20721&sectionno=15&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small`
  line `Industries Bank may, for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) issue and sell bonds and debentures with or without the guarantee of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) borrow money from the Reserve Bank--`
  line
  line `(i) repayable on demand or on the expiry of the fixed periods not exceeding ninety days from`
  line `the date on which the money is so borrowed against the security of stocks, funds and securities`
  line `(other than immovable property) in which a trustee is authorised to invest trust money by any law`
  line `for the time being in force in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) against bills of exchange or promissory notes arising out of bona fide commercial or trade`
  line `transactions, bearing two or more good signatures and maturing within five years from the date of`
  line `the borrowing;`
  line
  line `(iii) out of the National Industrial Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund established under`
  line `section 46C of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), for any of the purposes specified`
  line `in that section;`
  line
  line `(c) borrow money from the Development Bank or such other authority, organisation or institution`
  line `as may be generally or specially ^1[approved by the Board];`
  line
  line `(d) accept deposits repayable after the expiry of such period and on such terms as may be`
  line `generally or specially ^1[approved by the Board].`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on a request being made to it by the Small Industries Bank,`
  line `guarantee the bonds and debentures issued by that Bank as to the repayment of principal and the payment`
  line `of interest at such rate as may be fixed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20722)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 22
  title Investment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20722&sectionno=16&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Investment.-- The Small Industries Bank may invest (whether by way of deposits in banks or`
  line `otherwise) the amounts available in the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund or the Small`
  line `Industries General Fund or any other fund or account which are not for the time being required for the`
  line `transaction of business in such manner as may be approved by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20723)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to transfer rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20723&sectionno=17&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The rights and interests of the Small Industries Bank (including any`
  line `other rights incidental thereto) in relation to any loan or advance granted, or any amount recoverable, by it`
  line `may be transferred by the Small Industries Bank, either in whole or in part, by the execution or issue of`
  line `any instrument or by the transfer of any instrument by endorsement, or in any other manner in which the`
  line `rights and interests in relation to such loan or advance may be lawfully transferred, and the Small`
  line `Industries Bank may, notwithstanding such transfer, act as the trustee for the transferee.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20724)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to acquire rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20724&sectionno=18&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Small Industries Bank shall have the right to acquire, by transfer`
  line `on assignment the rights and interests of any public financial institution as defined in section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (including any other rights incidental thereto) in relation to any loan or`
  line `advance granted, or any amount recoverable by such institution, either in whole or in part, by the`
  line `execution or issue of any instrument or by the transfer of any instrument or in any other manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (20725)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 25
  title `Loan in foreign currency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20725&sectionno=19&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), or in any other enactment for the time being in force relating to`
  line `foreign exchange, the Small Industries Bank may, for the purposes of granting loans and advances under`
  line `this Act, borrow, with the previous consent of the Central Government 1`
  line `***, foreign currency from any`
  line `bank or financial institution in any foreign country or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, where necessary, guarantee any loan taken by the Small Industries`
  line `Bank under sub-section (1) or any part thereof as to the repayment of principal and the payment of`
  line `interest and other incidental charges.`
  line
  line `(3) All loans and advances granted by the Small Industries Bank out of foreign currency borrowed`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be expressed in terms of foreign currency as equivalent of Indian currency`
  line `calculated in accordance with the rate of exchange prevailing at the time of grant thereof, and the amount`
  line `due thereunder shall be repayable in equivalent Indian currency, calculated in accordance with the rate of`
  line `exchange prevailing at the time of repayment of such loan or advance.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless otherwise provided by the Central Government, any loss or profit in connection with any`
  line `borrowing of foreign currency under sub-section (1) for the purpose of granting loans and advances under`
  line `this Act, or with its repayment to the concerned foreign lending agency, on account of any fluctuations in`
  line `the exchange accruing--`
  line
  line `(a) during the period within which the loan or advance is repayable by the industrial concern in`
  line `the small-scale sector or the period of actual repayment thereof by the concern, whichever is longer,`
  line `shall be reimbursed by, or paid to, as the case may be, the recipient of such loans and advances;`
  line
  line `(b) after the expiry of the period specified in clause (a),--`
  line
  line `(i) shall be borne by the Small Industries Bank in respect of normal market fluctuations in the`
  line `rate of foreign exchange;`
  line
  line `(ii) shall be reimbursed by, or paid to, as the case may be, the Central Government in respect`
  line `of fluctuations other than the normal market fluctuations in foreign exchange.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--If any question arises as to whether any fluctuation as aforesaid is a normal market`
  line `fluctuation or not, the same shall be decided by the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (20726)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 26
  title `Grants, donations, etc., to the Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20726&sectionno=20&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Small Industries Bank may`
  line `receive gifts, grants, donations, benefactions or other monies from Government or any other source.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (20727)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 27
  title `Free transferability of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20727&sectionno=20A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Free transferability of shares.--(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the equity`
  line `shares of the Small Industries Bank shall be freely transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall entitle the Development Bank, the public sector banks,`
  line `the General Insurance Corporation, the Life Insurance Corporation and other institutions owned or`
  line `controlled by the Central Government to transfer any shares held by them in the Small Industries Bank if`
  line `such transfer will result in reducing the equity shares held in aggregate by them to less than fifty-one per`
  line `cent. of the issued equity share capital of the Small Industries Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b:
  sectionId (20728)
  sectionNo 20B
  orderNo 28
  title `Register of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20728&sectionno=20B&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[20B. Register of shareholders.--(1) The Small Industries Bank shall keep at its head office a`
  line `register, in one or more books, of the shareholders and shall enter therein the following particulars so far`
  line `as they may be available, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the names, addresses and occupations, if any, of the shareholders and a statement of the shares`
  line `held by each shareholder, distinguishing each share by its denoting number;`
  line
  line `(ii) the date on which each person is so entered as a shareholder;`
  line
  line `(iii) the date on which any person ceases to be a shareholder; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the shares held with a depository under the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Small Industries`
  line `Bank to keep the register of the shareholders in computer floppies, diskettes, compact disk or any other`
  line `electronic form, subject to such safeguards, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), a copy of, or`
  line `extract from, the register of the shareholders, certified to be a true copy under the hand of an officer of the`
  line `Small Industries Bank authorised in this behalf, shall, in all legal proceedings, be admissible in evidence.`
  line
  line `(4) The Register of beneficial owners maintained by a depository under section 11 of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) shall be deemed to be a Register of the shareholders for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_c:
  sectionId (20729)
  sectionNo 20C
  orderNo 29
  title `Trust not to be entered on the register of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20729&sectionno=20C&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[20C. Trust not to be entered on the register of shareholders.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 20B, no notice of any trust, express, implied or constructive, shall be entered on the`
  line `register of shareholders or be receivable by the Small Industries Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a depository in respect of the shares held by it as a`
  line `registered owner on behalf of a beneficial owner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of section 20B and this section, the expressions "beneficial owner",`
  line `"depository" and "registered owner" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (a),`
  line `(e) and (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_d:
  sectionId (20730)
  sectionNo 20D
  orderNo 30
  title `Board's right to refuse registration of transfer of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20730&sectionno=20D&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[20D. Board’s right to refuse registration of transfer of shares.--(1) The Board may refuse to`
  line `register the transfer of any shares in the name of the transferee on any one or more of the following`
  line `grounds, and on no other ground, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer of the shares is in contravention of the provisions of this Act or regulations made`
  line `thereunder or any other law;`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer of the shares, in the opinion of the Board, is prejudicial to the interests of the`
  line `Small Industries Bank or to the public interest;`
  line
  line `(c) the transfer of shares is prohibited by an order of a court, tribunal or any other authority under`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall, before the expiry of two months from the date on which the instrument of`
  line `transfer of shares of the Small Industries Bank is lodged with it for the purpose of registration of such`
  line `transfer, not only form, in good faith, its opinion as to whether such registration ought not or ought to be`
  line `refused on any of the grounds referred to in sub-section (1) but also,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it has formed the opinion that such registration ought not to be so refused, effect such`
  line `registration; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it has formed the opinion that such registration ought to be refused on any of the grounds`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1), intimate the transferor and the transferee by notice in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal against the order of refusal of the Board under sub-section (2) shall lie to the Central`
  line `Government and the procedure for filing and hearing of such appeal shall be in accordance with the rules`
  line `made by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_e:
  sectionId (20731)
  sectionNo 20E
  orderNo 31
  title `Shares to be securities under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20731&sectionno=20E&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[20E. Shares to be securities under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), the shares of the Small Industries Bank shall be`
  line `deemed to be included among the securities enumerated in section 20 of the said Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_f:
  sectionId (20732)
  sectionNo 20F
  orderNo 32
  title `Annual general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20732&sectionno=20F&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[20F. Annual general meeting.--(1) The Small Industries Bank shall in each year hold, in addition`
  line `to any other meetings, a general meeting as its annual general meeting and shall specify the meeting as`
  line `such in the notices calling it; and not more than fifteen months shall elapse between the date of one`
  line `annual general meeting and that of the next:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Small Industries Bank may hold the first annual general meeting within a period of`
  line `six months from the date on which it allots shares for the first time to public for subscription:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may extend the time within which any annual general`
  line `meeting shall be held by a period not exceeding three months.`
  line
  line `(2) Every annual general meeting shall be called for a time during business hours, on a day that is not`
  line `public holiday, and shall be held either at head office or at some other place within the city or town in`
  line `which the head office is situated.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "public holiday" means a public holiday within the`
  line `meaning of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881):`
  line
  line `Provided that no Sunday shall be deemed to be such a holiday in relation to any meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no day declared by the Central Government to be a public holiday shall be`
  line `deemed to be such a holiday, in relation to any meeting, unless the declaration was notified before the`
  line `issue of the notice convening such meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_g:
  sectionId (20733)
  sectionNo 20G
  orderNo 33
  title `Matters to be discussed and procedure in annual general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20733&sectionno=20G&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[20G. Matters to be discussed and procedure in annual general meeting.--(1) The shareholders`
  line `present at an annual general meeting shall be entitled to discuss and adopt--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance-sheet and profit and loss account of the Small Industries Bank made up to the date`
  line `on which its accounts are closed and balanced;`
  line
  line `(b) the report of working of the Small Industries Bank for the period covered by the accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) the auditors report on the balance-sheet and accounts;`
  line
  line `(d) proposals for declaration of dividend and capitalisation of reserves;`
  line
  line `(e) appointment of auditors referred to in sub-section (1) of section 30.`
  line
  line `(2) The shareholders present at an annual general meeting may also discuss any other matter to be`
  line `transacted at such meetings in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `(3) The matters relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which annual general meeting or other meetings are held under this Act and the`
  line `procedure to be followed thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which voting rights may be exercised and resolutions may be passed; and`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure for transaction of business at such meetings and related matters.`
  line
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (20734)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 34
  title `Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 13, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20734&sectionno=21&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, the Small Industries Bank shall establish and maintain, a`
  line `special fund to be called the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Small Industries Bank may, at any time, establish any fund as part of the Small Industries`
  line `Development Assistance Fund for such purpose or purposes as may be approved by the Central`
  line `Government on the recommendation of the ^1[Board], or establish any other fund as may be required by or`
  line `under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (20735)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 35
  title `Credits to Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20735&sectionno=22&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `To the Small Industries`
  line `Development Assistance Fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all amounts received for the purpose of that Fund by way of loans, gifts, grants, donations,`
  line `benefactions or otherwise from Government or any other source;`
  line
  line `(b) repayments or recoveries in respect of loans, advances or other facilities granted from the`
  line Fund;
  line
  line `(c) income or profits from investments made from the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) income accruing or arising to the Fund, by way of interest or otherwise, on account of the`
  line `application of the Fund in accordance with the provisions of section 23.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (20736)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 36
  title `Utilisation of Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20736&sectionno=23&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Small Industries Bank`
  line `may disburse or spend from the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund, any amount for such`
  line `purposes as the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the ^1[Board], specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (20737)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 37
  title `Debits to Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20737&sectionno=24&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the Small Industries`
  line `Development Assistance Fund shall be debited--`
  line
  line `(a) such amounts as may from time to time be disbursed or spend under section 23;`
  line
  line `(b) such amounts as may be required for discharging the liabilities in respect of loans received for`
  line `the purpose of that Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) any loss arising on account of investment made out of that Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) such expenditure arising out of, or in connection with, the administration and application of`
  line `that Fund as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) No amount shall be debited to the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund except as`
  line `provided for in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (20738)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 38
  title `Accounts and audit of Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20738&sectionno=25&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `balance-sheet and accounts of Small Industries Development Assistance Fund shall be prepared in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the Small Industries Development Assistance`
  line `Fund to be closed and balanced as on the 31st day of March, each year or such other date as the ^1[Board]`
  line `may specify.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The Small Industries Development Assistance Fund shall be audited by the auditors, appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 30, who shall make a separate report thereon.]`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 30 shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to the audit of the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  line
  line `(5) The Small Industries Bank shall furnish to the Central Government 5*** within four months from`
  line `the date on which the accounts of the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund are closed and`
  line `balanced, a copy of balance-sheet and accounts together with a copy of its auditors' report and a report on`
  line `the operation of that Fund during the relevant year and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after they are received by it, cause the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and the Development Bank" omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (20739)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 39
  title `Liquidation of Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. The words ", on the recommendation of the Development Bank" omitted by Act 7 of 2000, s. 16 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20739&sectionno=26&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Small Industries`
  line `Development Assistance Fund shall not be closed or wound up save by order of the Central Government`
  line `and in such manner as that Government may, 1*** direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (20740)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 40
  title `Small Industries General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20740&sectionno=27&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All receipts of the Small Industries Bank other than those`
  line `which are to be credited to the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund under this Act shall be`
  line `credited to a fund to be called the Small Industries General Fund and all payments by the Small Industries`
  line `Bank, other than those which are to be debited to the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund,`
  line `shall be made out of the Small Industries General Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (20741)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 41
  title `Preparation of accounts and balance-sheet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20741&sectionno=28&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank shall be prepared in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the Small Industries Bank to be closed and`
  line `balanced as on the 31st day of March each year or such other date, as the ^1[Board] may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (20742)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 42
  title `Disposal of profits accruing to Small Industries General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20742&sectionno=29&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small Industries`
  line `Bank may establish a reserve fund to which may be transferred such sums as that Bank may deem fit out`
  line `of the annual profits accruing to the Small Industries General Fund.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets and for all other`
  line `matters for which provision is necessary or expedient or which is usually provided for by bankers and for`
  line `the reserve fund referred to in sub-section (1), and after transferring a part of the profits to such other`
  line `reserves or funds as may be considered appropriate, the Board may, out of its net profits, propose a`
  line dividend.]
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (20743)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 43
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20743&sectionno=30&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)The accounts of the Small Industries Banks shall be audited by auditors duly`
  line `qualified to act as auditors under sub-section (1) of section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),`
  line `who shall be appointed by the Small Industries Bank in general meeting of the shareholders out of the`
  line `panel of auditors approved by the Reserve Bank for such term and on such remuneration as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may fix.]`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet of the Small Industries`
  line `Bank and it shall be their duty to examine it together with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto and`
  line `they shall have a list delivered to them of all books kept by the Small Industries Bank and shall at all`
  line `reasonable times have access to the books, accounts, vouchers and other documents of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors may, in relation to such accounts, examine any Director or any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Small Industries Bank and shall be entitled to require from the Board or officers or other`
  line `employees of the Small Industries Bank such information and explanation as they may think necessary for`
  line `the performance of their duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditors shall make a report to the Small Industries Bank upon the annual balance-sheet and`
  line `accounts examined by them and in every such report they shall state whether in their opinion the`
  line `balance-sheet is a full and fair balance-sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so`
  line `as to exhibit a true and fair view of the state of affairs of the Small Industries Bank and in case they had`
  line `called for any explanation or information from the Board or any officer or other employee of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank whether it has been given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(5) The Small Industries Bank shall furnish to the Central Government ^1*** within four months from`
  line `the date on which its accounts are closed and balanced, a copy of its balance-sheet and accounts together`
  line `with a copy of the auditors report and a report of the working of the Small Industries Bank during the`
  line `relevant year, and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be after they are received by it, cause the`
  line `same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and the Development Bank" omitted by Act 7 of 2000, s. 19 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (20744)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 44
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20744&sectionno=31&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4) of section 25, nothing contained in this`
  line `Chapter shall apply to the Small Industries Development Assistance Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (20745)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 45
  title `Transfer of part of business of Development Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20745&sectionno=32&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) On such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, the business, assets and liabilities, rights, interests, privileges`
  line `and obligations of the Development Bank relating to the Small Industries Development Fund and the`
  line `National Equity Fund (hereinafter in this section referred to as Fund) shall stand transferred to, and vest`
  line `in, the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Small Industries Development Fund" and "National Equity Fund" mean the Small`
  line `Industries Development Fund and National Equity Fund referred to as such in the books and accounts of`
  line `the Development Bank on the day immediately preceding the date appointed in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Small Industries Bank under sub-section (1) of the Funds,`
  line `that Bank shall pay to the Development Bank such amount and on such terms and conditions as the`
  line `Development Bank may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) All contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of attorney, grants of legal representation and`
  line `other instruments of whatever nature which relate to the Funds and which are subsisting or having effect`
  line `immediately before the date referred to in sub-section (1) and to which the Development Bank is a party`
  line `or which are in favour of the Development Bank shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if they relate exclusively to the Funds, be of full force and effect against or in favour of the`
  line `Small Industries Bank and may be enforced and acted upon as fully and effectively as if, instead of`
  line `the Development Bank, the Small Industries Bank had been a party thereto or as if they had been`
  line `issued in favour of the Small Industries Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) if they relate not only to the Funds but also to any of the other business or functions of the`
  line `Development Bank, be of full force and effect against or in favour of both the Development Bank and`
  line `the Small Industries Bank and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectively as if, in addition`
  line `to the Development Bank, the Small Industries Bank had also been a party thereto or as if they had`
  line `been issued in favour of the Development Bank and also the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the date referred to in sub-section (1), any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever`
  line `nature relating to the Funds is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any way`
  line `prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer to the Small Industries Bank of the business of the`
  line `Development Bank or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may,--`
  line
  line `(a) where it relates exclusively to the Funds, be continued prosecuted and enforced by or against`
  line `the Small Industries Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) where it relates not only to the Funds but also to any of the other business or functions of the`
  line `Development Bank be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Development Bank and`
  line `the Small Industries Bank or, if the Central Government by order in writing so directs, by or against`
  line `such one of them, as may be specified in such order.`
  line
  line `(5) If any question arises as to whether any contract, deed, bond, agreement, power of attorney, grant`
  line `of legal representation or other instrument referred to in sub-section (3) or any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding referred to in sub-section (4) relates or relate exclusively to the Funds it shall be referred to`
  line `the Development Bank for decision and the decision of the Development Bank thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964), or any other law or any instrument having`
  line `force by virtue of the said Act or other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (20746)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 46
  title `Staff of Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20746&sectionno=33&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small Industries Bank may appoint such number of`
  line `officers and other employees as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its`
  line `functions and determine the terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `(2) At any time before the expiry of six months from the appointed day, the Development Bank may,`
  line `in public interest, transfer to the Small Industries Bank such members of its staff whom the Development`
  line `Bank considers as relevant to, or suitable for, the functions of the Small Industries Bank, as on deputation`
  line `with the Small Industries Bank, but such members shall hold office by the same tenure and upon the same`
  line `terms and conditions of service as respects remuneration, leave, provident fund, retirement or other`
  line `terminal benefits as they would have held such office if the Small Industries Bank had not been`
  line `established and shall continue to do so until the Development Bank either on its own motion or at the`
  line `request of the Small Industries Bank recalls such member of staff to its service:`
  line
  line `Provided that every member of the staff so transferred may elect to go back to the Development Bank`
  line `by exercising an option in writing to that effect before the expiry of a period of nine months from the`
  line `appointed day and on the exercise of such option, the Development Bank shall, before the expiration of a`
  line `period of eighteen months from the appointed day, take back such member of the staff and he shall be`
  line `deemed to have been on deputation to the Small Industries Bank during the period he was a member of`
  line `the staff of the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the absorption of any member of the staff by the Small Industries`
  line `Bank in its regular service under this section shall not entitle such employee to any compensation under`
  line `that Act or other law and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "appointed day" means the date of establishment of`
  line `the Small Industries Bank under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (20747)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 47
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20747&sectionno=34&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order, delegate to any Director or`
  line `committee constituted under section 12 or to any officer or other employee of the Small Industries Bank,`
  line `subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and`
  line `duties under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (20748)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 48
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 20, for "the Central Government, the Reserve Bank and the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20748&sectionno=35&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Small Industries Bank shall furnish from time to time to ^1[the Central`
  line `Government and the Reserve Bank] such returns as they may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (20749)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 49
  title `Obligations as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20749&sectionno=36&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small Industries Bank shall not, except as`
  line `otherwise required by this Act or any other law, divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs of, its`
  line `constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in accordance with the law or practice and usage`
  line `customary among bankers necessary or appropriate for the Small Industries Bank to divulge such`
  line information.
  line
  line `(2) The Small Industries Bank may, for the purpose of the efficient discharge of the functions under`
  line `this Act, collect from or furnish to the Central Government, Reserve Bank, Development Bank, State`
  line `Bank, any subsidiary bank, nationalised bank or other scheduled bank, State Cooperative Bank, State`
  line `Financial Corporation, State Industrial Development Corporation, State Small Industries Corporation or`
  line
  line `the National Small Industries Corporation or such other institutions ^1[as may be specified by the Board],`
  line `credit information or other information as it may consider useful for the purpose, in such manner and at`
  line `such times, as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression "credit information" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as in clause (c) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), subject`
  line `to the modification that "banking company" referred to therein shall mean a bank, corporation or other`
  line `institution referred to in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Director, member of a committee, auditor, officer or other employee of the Small Industries`
  line `Bank ^2*** whose services are utilised by the Small Industries Bank under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out in the`
  line `First Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 21, for as "may be specified by the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the Development Bank" omitted by s. 21, ibid., (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (20750)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 50
  title `Defects in appointment not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20750&sectionno=37&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board or of`
  line `any committee of the Small Industries Bank shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of`
  line `any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board or the committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a Director shall be deemed to be invalid merely`
  line `on the ground that he was disqualified to be a Director or that there was any other defect in his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (20751)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 51
  title `Amounts and securities to be held in trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20751&sectionno=37A&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[37A. Amounts and securities to be held in trust.--(1) Any sums received by a borrowing`
  line `institution in repayment or realisation of loans and advances refinanced either wholly or partly by the`
  line `Small Industries Bank shall, to the extent of the accommodation granted by the Small Industries Bank and`
  line `remaining outstanding, be deemed to have been received by the borrowing institution in trust for the`
  line `Small Industries Bank, and shall accordingly be paid by such institution to the Small Industries Bank, as`
  line `per the repayment schedule fixed by the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an accommodation has been granted to a borrowing institution, all securities held, or which`
  line `may be held, by such borrowing institution, on account of any transaction in respect of which such`
  line `accommodation has been granted by the Small Industries Bank, shall be held by such institution in trust`
  line `for the Small Industries Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (20752)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 52
  title `Rights of Small Industries Bank in case of default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20752&sectionno=38&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any industrial concern in the`
  line `small-scale sector, which is under a liability to the Small Industries Bank under an agreement, makes any`
  line `default in repayment of any loan or advance or any instalment thereof or in meeting its obligations in`
  line `relation to any guarantee given by the Small Industries Bank or otherwise fails to comply with the terms`
  line `of its agreement, with the Small Industries Bank, the Small Industries Bank shall have the right to take`
  line `over the management, or possession, or both of such industrial concern in the small-scale sector, as well`
  line `as the right to transfer by way of lease or sale and realise the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated`
  line `or assigned to the Small Industries Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Any transfer of property made by the Small Industries Bank, in exercise of its powers under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall vest in the transferee all rights in or to the property transferred as if the transfer had`
  line `been made by the owner of the property.`
  line
  line `(3) The Small Industries Bank shall have the same rights and powers with respect to goods`
  line `manufactured or produced wholly or partly from goods forming part of the security held by it as it had`
  line `with respect to the original goods.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any action has been taken against an industrial concern in the small-scale sector under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), all costs, charges and expenses which in the opinion of the Small Industries`
  line `Bank have been properly incurred by it as incidental thereto shall be recoverable from the industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector and the money which is received by it shall, in the absence of any`
  line `contract to the contrary, be held by it in trust to be applied firstly, in payment of such costs, charges and expenses and, secondly, in discharge of the debt due to the Small Industries Bank, and the residue of the`
  line `money so received shall be paid to the person entitled thereto in accordance with his rights and interests.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Small Industries Bank takes over the management or possession of an industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector under the provisions of sub-section (1), the Small Industries Bank shall`
  line `be deemed to be the owner of such concern, for the purposes of suits by or against the concern, and shall`
  line `sue and be sued in the name of the concern.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (20753)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power to seek assistance of Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20753&sectionno=39&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property, effects or actionable claims are sold or leased in pursuance of any`
  line `power conferred by section 38, the Small Industries Bank or any other person authorised by it may, for`
  line `the purpose of taking into custody or under control any such property, effects or actionable claims,`
  line `request, in writing, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate within whose jurisdiction`
  line `any such property, effects, actionable claims, books of account or other documents relating thereto may`
  line `be situated or found, to take possession thereof, and the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District`
  line `Magistrate shall, on such request being made to him,--`
  line
  line `(a) take possession of such property, effects, actionable claims, or books of account or other`
  line `documents relating thereto; and`
  line
  line `(b) forward them to the Small Industries Bank or such other person, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of securing compliance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate may take or cause to be taken such steps and use, or`
  line `cause to be used, such force as may, in his opinion, be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) No act of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate done in pursuance of this`
  line `section shall be called in question in any court or before any authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (20754)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20754&sectionno=40&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any`
  line `agreement to the contrary, the Small Industries Bank may, by notice in writing, require any industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector to which it has granted any loan or advance to discharge forthwith in full`
  line `its liabilities to the Small Industries Bank,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Board that false or misleading information in any material particular was`
  line `given in the application for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the industrial concern in the small-scale sector has failed to comply with the terms of its`
  line `contract with the Small Industries Bank in the matter of the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the industrial concern in the small-scale sector is`
  line `unable to pay its debt or that proceedings for liquidation may be commenced in respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the Small Industries Bank as`
  line `security for the loan or advance is not insured and kept insured by the industrial concern in the smallscale`
  line `sector to the satisfaction of the Small Industries Bank; or depreciates in value to such an extent`
  line `that, in the opinion of the Board, further security to the satisfaction of the Board should be given and`
  line `such security is not given; or`
  line
  line `(e) if, without the permission of the Board, any machinery, plant or other equipment, whether`
  line `forming part of the security or otherwise, is removed from the premises of the industrial concern in`
  line `the small-scale sector without being replaced; or`
  line
  line `(f) if for any reason it is necessary to protect the interests of the Small Industries Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (20755)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 55
  title `Special provisions for enforcement of claims by Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20755&sectionno=41&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an`
  line `industrial concern in the small-scale sector, in breach of any agreement, makes any default in repayment`
  line `of any loan or advance or any instalment thereof or in meeting its obligations in relation to any guarantee`
  line `given by the Small Industries Bank or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of its agreement with that`
  line `Bank, or where the Small Industries Bank requires any industrial concern in the small-scale sector to`
  line `make repayment of any loan or advance under section 40 and such industrial concern fails to make such repayment, then, without prejudice to the provisions of section 38 of this Act and section 69 of the`
  line `Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), any officer of that Bank, generally or specially authorised by`
  line `that Bank in this behalf, may apply, to the Court for one or more of the following reliefs, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for an order for the sale of the property assigned, charged, hypothecated, mortgaged or`
  line `pledged to that Bank as security for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) for enforcing the liability of any surety; or`
  line
  line `(c) for an ad interim injunction restraining the industrial concern in the small-scale sector from`
  line `transferring or removing its machinery, plant or equipment from the premises of such industrial`
  line `concern without the permission of the Small Industries Bank, where such transfer or removal is`
  line apprehended.
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall state the nature and extent of the liability of the`
  line `industrial concern in the small-scale sector to the Small Industries Bank, the ground on which it is made`
  line `and such other particulars as may be necessary for obtaining the relief prayed for.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the application is for the reliefs mentioned in clause (a) and clause (c) of sub-section (1),`
  line `the Court shall pass an ad interim order attaching the security, or so much of the property of the industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector as would on being sold realise in its estimation an amount equivalent in`
  line `value to the outstanding liability of such industrial concern to the Small Industries Bank together with`
  line `costs of the proceedings taken under this section with or without an ad interim injunction restraining such`
  line `industrial concern from transferring or removing its machinery, plant or equipment.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the application is for the relief mentioned in clause (b) of sub-section (1), the Court shall`
  line `issue a notice calling upon the surety to show cause on a date to be specified in the notice as to why the`
  line `liability should not be enforced.`
  line
  line `(5) Before passing any order under sub-section (3) or issuing a notice under sub-section (4), the Court`
  line `may, if it thinks fit, examine the officer making the application.`
  line
  line `(6) At the same time as it passes an order under sub-section (3), the Court shall issue to the industrial`
  line `concern in the small-scale sector or to the owner of the security attached, a notice accompanied by copies`
  line `of the order, the application and the evidence, if any, recorded by the Court calling upon such industrial`
  line `concern or owner, to show cause on a date to be specified in the notice, as to why the ad interim order of`
  line `attachment should not be made absolute or the injunction confirmed.`
  line
  line `(7) If no cause is shown, on or before the date specified in the notice under sub-section (4), the Court`
  line `shall forthwith order the enforcement of the liability of the surety.`
  line
  line `(8) If no cause is shown on or before the date specified in the notice under sub-section (6), the Court`
  line `shall forthwith make the ad interim order absolute and direct the sale of the attached property or confirm`
  line `the injunction.`
  line
  line `(9) If cause is shown, the Court shall proceed to investigate the claim of the Small Industries Bank in`
  line `accordance with the provisions contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in so far as`
  line `such provisions may be applied thereto.`
  line
  line `(10) After making an investigation under sub-section (9), the Court may--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm the order of attachment and direct the sale of the attached property;`
  line
  line `(b) vary the order of attachment so as to release a portion of the property from attachment and`
  line `direct the sale of the remainder of the attached property;`
  line
  line `(c) release the property from attachment;`
  line
  line `(d) confirm or dissolve the injunction; or`
  line
  line `(e) direct the enforcement of the liability of the surety or reject the claim made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that when making an order under clause (c) or making an order rejecting the claim to`
  line `enforce the liability of the surety under clause (e), the Court may make such further order as it thinks necessary to protect the interests of the Small Industries Bank and may apportion the cost of the`
  line `proceedings in such manner as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that unless the Small Industries Bank intimates to the Court that it will not appeal`
  line `against any order releasing any property from attachment or rejecting the claim to enforce the liability of`
  line `the surety, such order shall not be given effect to, until the expiry of the period fixed under`
  line `sub-section (12) within which an appeal may be preferred or, if an appeal is preferred, unless the Court`
  line `empowered to hear appeals from the decisions of the said Court otherwise directs, until the appeal is`
  line `disposed of.`
  line
  line `(11) An order of attachment or sale of property under this section shall be carried into effect as far as`
  line `practicable in the manner provided in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the attachment or`
  line `sale of property in execution of a decree as if the Small Industries Bank were the decree holder.`
  line
  line `(12) Any party aggrieved by an order under sub-section (7), sub-section (8) or sub-section (10) may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date of the order, appeal to the Court empowered to hear appeals from the`
  line `decisions of the Court which passed the order and upon such appeal the appellate Court may, after hearing`
  line `the parties, pass such orders as it thinks proper.`
  line
  line `(13) Where proceedings for liquidation in respect of an industrial concern in the small-scale sector`
  line `have commenced before an application is made under sub-section (1), nothing in this section shall be`
  line `construed as giving to the Small Industries Bank any preference over the other creditors of such industrial`
  line `concern not conferred on it by any other law.`
  line
  line `(14) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any Court competent to grant an ad interim`
  line `injunction under this section shall also have the power to appoint a receiver and to exercise all the other`
  line `powers incidental thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (20756)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 56
  title `Small Industries Bank to have access to records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20756&sectionno=42&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Small Industries Bank shall have`
  line `free access to all such records of any institution which seeks to avail of any credit facilities from the`
  line `Small Industries Bank and to all such records of any such person who seeks to avail of any credit facilities`
  line `from such institution, perusal whereof may appear to the Small Industries Bank to be necessary in`
  line `connection with the providing of finance or other assistance to such institution or the refinancing of any`
  line `loan or advance made to such person by the borrowing institution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Small Industries Bank may require any institution or person referred to in sub-section (1) to`
  line `furnish to it copies of any of the records referred to in that sub-section and the institution or the person, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be bound to comply with such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (20757)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 57
  title `Validity of loan or advance not to be questioned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20757&sectionno=43&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, the validity of any loan or advance granted by the`
  line `Small Industries Bank in pursuance of the provisions of this Act shall not be called in question merely on`
  line `the ground of non-compliance with the requirements of such other law as aforesaid or of any resolution,`
  line `contract, memorandum, articles of association or other instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall render valid any loan or advance obtained by any company`
  line `or co-operative society where such company or co-operative society is not empowered by its`
  line `memorandum to obtain loans or advances.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (20758)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 58
  title `Indemnity of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20758&sectionno=44&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Director shall be indemnified by the Small Industries Bank`
  line `against all losses and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties, except`
  line `such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A Director shall not be responsible for any other Director or for any officer or other employee of`
  line `the Small Industries Bank or for any loss or expenses resulting to the Small Industries Bank or from the`
  line `insufficiency or deficiency of the value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or taken on behalf`
  line `of the Small Industries Bank or the insolvency or wrongful act of any debtor or any person under`
  line `obligation to the Small Industries Bank or anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his`
  line `office or in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (20759)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 59
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 23, for "chairman" (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20759&sectionno=45&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the Small Industries Bank, ^1[chairman and managing director, the whole-time director] or any Director or`
  line `any officer or other employee of such Bank or any other person authorised by that Bank to discharge any`
  line `functions under this Act for any loss or damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any other law or provision having the`
  line `force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (20760)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 60
  title `Nomination by depositors or holders of bonds or other securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20760&sectionno=46&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law, where a nomination in respect of any deposits, bonds or other`
  line `securities kept with or issued by the Small Industries Bank is made in the prescribed manner, the amount`
  line `due on such deposits, bonds or other securities shall, on the death of the depositor or holder thereof, vest`
  line `in, and be payable to, the nominee subject to any right, title, interest or claim of any other person, in`
  line `relation to such deposits, bonds or other securities.`
  line
  line `(2) Any payment by the Small Industries Bank in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be a full discharge of its liability in respect of such deposits, bonds or securities.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (20761)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 61
  title `Arrangement with Small Industries Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20761&sectionno=47&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `any arrangement entered into by the Small Industries Bank with an industrial concern in the small-scale`
  line `sector provides for the appointment by the Small Industries Bank of one or more directors of such industrial`
  line `concern, such provision and any appointment of directors made in pursuance, thereof shall be valid and`
  line `effective notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum, articles of association or any other`
  line `instrument relating to that industrial concern, and any provision regarding share qualification, age-limit,`
  line `number of directorships, removal from office of directors and such like conditions contained in any such`
  line `law or instrument aforesaid, shall not apply to any director appointed by the Small Industries Bank in`
  line `pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the Small Industries Bank and may be removed or`
  line `substituted by any person by order in writing of the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (20762)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 62
  title `Act 18 of 1891 to apply in relation to Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20762&sectionno=48&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The Bankers' Books Evidence`
  line `Act, 1891 shall apply in relation to Small Industries Bank as if it were a bank as defined in section 2 of`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (20763)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 63
  title `Act 10 of 1949 not to apply to Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20763&sectionno=49&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949, except section 34A and section 36AD thereof, shall apply to the Small Industries`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (20764)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 64
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20764&sectionno=50&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `[Act 43 of 1961 not to apply to Small Industries Bank.]--Omitted by the Finance Act, 2001`
  line `(14 of 2001), s. 142 (w.e.f 1-4-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (20765)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 65
  title `Liquidation of Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20765&sectionno=51&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies or corporations shall apply to the Small Industries Bank and that Bank shall not be placed in`
  line `liquidation save by order of the Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51_a:
  sectionId (20766)
  sectionNo 51A
  orderNo 66
  title `Power to make rules by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2000, s. 24 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20766&sectionno=51A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_51_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[51 A. Power to make rules by Central Government.-- (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for filing and hearing of appeal against the refusal to register the transfer of`
  line `shares by the Board under sub-section (3) of section 20D; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed by rules under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (20767)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587&sectionId=20767&sectionno=52&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00035_198939_1517807323587
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may ^1***`
  line `by notification, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or`
  line `expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the removal of Director under sub-section (8) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(aa) the places of meetings of the Board under this Act and the procedure to be followed at such`
  line `meetings including the quorum necessary for transaction of business and the manner of adoption of`
  line `resolution under section 6;`
  line
  line `(ab) the functions to be discharged by the Executive Committee under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(ac) the places of meetings of the Executive Committee and the procedure to be followed at such`
  line `meetings under sub-section (4) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(ad) such fees and allowances which may be paid to the directors and members of the Executive`
  line `Committee under section 12A;`
  line
  line `(ae) the particulars to be prescribed in the register of shareholders under clause (iv) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 20B;`
  line
  line `(af) the procedure relating to maintenance of register of shareholders in electronic form under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 20B;`
  line
  line `(ag) the matters relating to the annual general meeting under sub-section (3) of section 20G;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which the balance-sheets and the accounts of the Small Industries`
  line `Development Assistance Fund under sub-section (1) of section 25 and the Small Industries Bank`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 28 shall be prepared;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which nominations may be made in terms of sub-section (1) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(d) generally the efficient conduct of the affairs of the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government, and every regulation made by the Board under this`
  line `Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in`
  line `session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous approval of the Development Bank" omitted by Act 7 of 2000, s. 25 (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 27-3-2000).`
